# 🎶 Career Journeys in the Curriculum

## Why Career Journeys?

Help students connect CS to the real world through inspiring stories from music and tech professionals. These role models reflect diverse voices and show many ways into CS careers.

## Lesson Spotlights
<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; width: 100%;">

<!-- Lesson 1 -->
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; width: 100%;">
<img src="https://images.code.org/b1e4ca3e722641a13fd296d462544ab5-image-1747758631405.png" alt="Shakira" style="width: 10%; border-radius: 10px; margin: 0px 20px 20px 0px;">
<div>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0;">Lesson 1: Songwriter’s Toolbox</p>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin: 5px 0;"><i>Featuring Shakira</i><br>Songwriters → Programmers: Both use sequence to tell stories.</p>
</div>
</div>

<!-- Lesson 2 -->
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; width: 100%;">
<img src="https://images.code.org/d0a65be85406bbf005d6e080a01cd029-image-1747759032726.36.00 AM.png" alt="Henny da Bizness" style="width: 10%; border-radius: 10px; margin: 0px 20px 20px 0px;">
<div>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0;">Lesson 2: Producer Power</p>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin: 5px 0;"><i>Featuring Henny da Bizness</i><br>Producers reuse beats → Programmers reuse code (functions).</p>
</div>
</div>

<!-- Lesson 3 -->
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; width: 100%;">
<img src="https://images.code.org/7c8b5827590d965e79a1439697c514ed-image-1747758977924.34.36 AM.png" alt="Roxanne" style="width: 10%; border-radius: 10px; margin: 0px 20px 20px 0px;">
<div>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; margin: 0;">Lesson 3: Sound Designer’s Studio</p>
<p style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.2; margin: 5px 0;"><i>Featuring Roxanne</i><br>Sound effects react to player actions → Like event-driven code.</p>
</div>
</div>

</div>

## 📚 Bring It to Your Classroom

<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 10px; width: 100%; margin: 20px auto;">

<!-- Card 1 -->
<div style="background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); text-align: center;">
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;">👩🏽‍💻 Show Diverse Role Models</p>
<ul style="font-size: 13pt; text-align: left;">
<li>Share stories from all backgrounds</li>
<li>Include non-traditional tech paths</li>
</ul>
</div>

<!-- Card 2 -->
<div style="background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); text-align: center;">
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;">🎨 Link CS to Student Passions</p>
<ul style="font-size: 13pt; text-align: left;">
<li>Start with what they love (music, fashion, sports)</li>
<li>Use hands-on, creative projects</li>
</ul>
</div>

<!-- Card 3 -->
<div style="background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); text-align: center;">
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;">🧭 Explore Career Paths</p>
<ul style="font-size: 13pt; text-align: left;">
<li>Tech is more than coding</li>
<li>Talk about college, bootcamps, and more</li>
</ul>
</div>

<!-- Card 4 -->
<div style="background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); text-align: center;">
<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;">🌱 Celebrate Growth</p>
<ul style="font-size: 13pt; text-align: left;">
<li>Normalize mistakes</li>
<li>Share your own learning</li>
<li>Value effort and creativity</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
